{"title":"Review: Delta Cycles handlebar smartphone mounts offer tough, lightweight options for screen time","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/17/review-delta-cycles-handlebar-smartphone-mounts-offer-tough-lightweight-options-for-screen-time/","date":1615982445000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Until now, Delta Cycle was known more for wall- and floor-mounted bicycle storage options, making it easy to rack your bike in the garage (or living room). Now, they’re making it just as easy to rack your phone to your handlebar.</p><p>We tested their new X-Pro and Holder models, which offer two completely different methods for securing your phone to your bicycle. Each has multiple options, with the X-Pro also offering a steerer tube spacer mount design that keeps the phone closer in.</p><p>If you’re looking for a quick, easy, and secure way to use your smartphone for navigation while riding, check these out…</p><h3>Delta X-Mount Pro Handlebar Smartphone Mount</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03.jpg\" alt=\"delta cycle x pro handlebar mount universal smartphone holder\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-629x420.jpg 629w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075735/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-03-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a></p><p>The Delta X-Mount Pro gets its name from the X-shaped silicone band that gives it a universal fit. We tested it with plus-sized iPhone 8 and X, both with a thicker case, and it fit and held just fine.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>The straps come close to the buttons on either side of an iPhone, but don’t quite hit them if you position everything correctly. They’re firm, and maintain solid grip on the phone.</p><p>Yes, it’s a little weird sticking a $1,000 phone off the front of your bike on a lightweight alloy beam with stretchy bands holding it in place. But I rode it over potholes and big cracks in the street, through drain dips, and over any normal bump I could find in our downtown. The phone held steady and didn’t bounce or shift at all.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01.jpg\" alt=\"delta cycle x mount pro universal smartphone holder for bicycle handlebars shown with actual weight and all accessories\" width=\"1420\" height=\"828\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1420px) 100vw, 1420px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01.jpg 1420w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-800x466.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-768x448.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-696x406.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-1068x623.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-720x420.jpg 720w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01.jpg 1420w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-800x466.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-768x448.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-696x406.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-1068x623.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075718/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-01-720x420.jpg 720w\"></a></p><p>What makes the X-Mount Pro standout from other mounts is the included accessories and addition of an anti-rotation beam. First, the accessories:<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><p>Want to run a Garmin or Wahoo instead of your phone? No problem, just unbolt the phone mount and swap in one of the included GPS cycling computer mounts. With almost every brand of cycling head unit using either Garmin- or Wahoo-compatible mounting tabs, this mount should work with just about anything.</p><p>The actual mount comes in a just 42g, and Delta’s claimed weight with the anti-rotation beam is 50g. Quite light for such a big mount.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04.jpg\" alt=\"delta cycle x pro handlebar mount universal smartphone holder\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075751/delta-cycles-x-mount-bar-pro-handlebar-phone-mount-review-04-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Fortunately, that lightweight didn’t make it flimsy. The T-shaped beam offered enough support to keep the phone steady. One thing we rarely see on any mounts is an anti-rotation system, but with so much weight out front, this one’s key.</p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>Delta’s mount is slotted on the inside of the bar clamping area, and that slides over a plastic guide that bends to rest under the stem. The L-shaped protrusion rests against the bottom of the stem, and once you clamp the mount onto it, the slotted design prevents it from spinning on the bar. So, your phone won’t droop a little every time you hit a bump.</p><p>Retail is $59.99, available direct and <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08D735S3Z?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">on Amazon</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1.jpg\" alt=\"delta x mount pro bicycle smartphone mount for steerer cap\" width=\"1200\" height=\"799\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-631x420.jpg 631w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16133129/delta-cycle-x-mount-pro-steerer-cap-mount-1-631x420.jpg 631w\"></a></p><p>They also offer the X-Mount Pro Low Profile (<em>$24.99, possibly <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07BB2HN8J?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">less on Amazon</a></em>) phone holder that slides over your steerer tube and gets locked into place with the headset’s top cap.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span>