r.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075644/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-02-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075644/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-02-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075644/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-02-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075644/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-02-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075644/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-02-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The Phone Holders use a stretch cord to capture your phone, and the XL extends to fit plus-sized phones with a case on, up to 3.5″ wide. There’s also a Hefty+ Phone Holder for phones/cases up to 4.5″ wide. All of them surround the phone and should protect it from scratches (or worse) if you wreck.</p><p>Clever features like rubber pads on the corners keep your phone from rattling inside it, and ports on the bottom let the speakers blast through for clear sound.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03.jpg\" alt=\"delta xl smartphone holder for bicycle handlebar mounts\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16075701/delta-cycles-deluxe-phone-holder-review-03-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Once your phone is inside, a patented cam lever locks it shut so there’s no way it would stretch open while riding. Honestly, I’m not sure how that would happen anyway, but this provides peace of mind that your phone will absolutely not bounce out no matter what.</p><p>The Phone Holder comes with a plastic top cap mount to replace your steerer tube’s cap if you prefer to have it centered over the stem. Otherwise, it clamps around your handlebar and secures with a bolt.</p><p>A second bolt allows for angle adjustment once installed, which is more useful than you’d think when you’re trying to get just the right position while also jockeying for space around everything else on the bar.</p><p>Retail ranges from $31.99 to $41.99 depending on size.</p><p><a href=\"https://designbydelta.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>DesignByDelta.com</em></a></p><p><em>Disclosure: Some of these links are affiliate links that may earn a small commission for Bikerumor if you click on them and buy something. This helps support our work here without costing you anything extra. You can learn more about <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/revenue-disclosures/\">how we make money here</a>. Thanks!</em></p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"589f4a379dfd97022450e0b412cd0c471ed37dc56b5d553316dee0afe41a12e5","category":"Cycling"}